True innovation takes many perspectives. To create products for everyone in the world, we need a workforce with different backgrounds and experiences. Apple is a diverse collective of problem solvers and doers, continually reimagining what’s possible to help us all do what we love in new ways. The same innovation that goes into our products also applies to our practices — strengthening our commitment to leave the world better than we found it. This is where your work can make a difference in people’s lives. Including your own.
Come join us, and be part of an extraordinary engineering team that will challenge, encourage, and drive you to be better every day. Additional opportunities may be available in our San Diego, CA location. 
Key Qualifications 
Some of the relevant degrees include: Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Computer/Software Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Data Science, Design, Industrial & Systems Engineering, Physics, Optical Engineering, Applied Sciences, Physics, Materials Engineering or related degrees 
Excellent written and verbal communication skills 
Able to collaborate across teams and external vendors to achieve project goals 
